The body of 76-year-old Sam Ballim was found by his sister at his Albatross home last week. JOHANNESBURG - Two men and a woman have been arrested for the murder of a pensioner in Lenasia in southern Johannesburg.Police say the body of 76-year-old Sam Ballim was found by his sister at his Albatross home last week. Spokesperson Hector Netshivodza says police are investigating the motive for the murder. Lenasia SAPS managed to arrest three suspects who are between the ages of 17 and 46. The suspects were wanted for killing a 76-year-old man. One of the suspects is his nephew. The three suspects are going to appear at the Soweto Magistrates Court today. 